## Every file and its responsibilities

### `apps/server/src/`
```
src/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ main.ts                    в†ђ bootstrap NestJS app, apply helmet/cors/pipes, listen on port
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ app.module.ts              в†ђ root module: imports all feature modules + ConfigModule + PrismaModule
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ modules/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queue/
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queue.module.ts    в†ђ declares QueueController, QueueService, QueueGateway; imports BullMQ queues
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queue.controller.tsв†ђ REST: POST /merchants/:id/queue (join), POST /queue/:id/arrived (redeem OTP)
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         GET  /merchants/:id/queue/:token (status)
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         POST /merchants/:id/queue/:token/advance (merchant advances)
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ queue.service.ts   в†ђ joinQueue() вЂ” atomic $transaction: lock QueueState, increment nextToken, insert QueueEntry
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         callNext() вЂ” pop from Redis list, mark called, start missed timer via BullMQ
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         redeemToken(otp) вЂ” validate OTP/QR, mark served
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         handleMissed(entryId) вЂ” BullMQ job processor: reinsert behind current position, notify user
в”‚   в”‚   в”‚                         getStatus(tokenId) вЂ” fetch entry + position
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ queue.gateway.ts   в†ђ WebSocket gateway: joinRoom(merchantId), emits queue_updated / position_changed
в”‚   в”‚
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ merchants/
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ merchants.module.ts
в”‚   в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ merchants.controller.ts в†ђ POST /merchants (register), GET /merchants?category=&lat=&lng= (list nearby)
в”‚   в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ merchants.service.ts    в†ђ createMerchant(), findNearby(lat, lng, category) using PostGIS or haversine
в”‚   в”‚
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ users/
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ users.module.ts
в”‚       в”њв”Ђв”Ђ users.controller.ts в†ђ POST /users (register/upsert by phone)
в”‚       в””в”Ђв”Ђ users.service.ts    в†ђ upsertUser(phone, name), updatePushToken()
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ prisma/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ prisma.module.ts       в†ђ Global module that exports PrismaService
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ prisma.service.ts      в†ђ extends PrismaClient, onModuleInit() connects, onModuleDestroy() disconnects
в”‚
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ redis/
в”‚   в”њв”Ђв”Ђ redis.module.ts        в†ђ provides IORedis instance via factory using ConfigService
в”‚   в””в”Ђв”Ђ redis.config.ts        в†ђ reads REDIS_URL from env, returns IORedis connection options
в”‚
в””в”Ђв”Ђ config/
    в””в”Ђв”Ђ app.config.ts          в†ђ ConfigModule.forRoot() schema: DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, JWT_SECRET, FCM_KEY, PORT
```

### `apps/server/` (alongside `src/`)
```
prisma/
в”њв”Ђв”Ђ schema.prisma              в†ђ you already have this, add @@index([merchantId]) on QueueEntry
в””в”Ђв”Ђ migrations/                в†ђ generated by prisma migrate dev

Dockerfile                     в†ђ multi-stage: builder (npm ci + tsc) в†’ runner (node dist/main)
.env.example                   в†ђ DATABASE_URL=, REDIS_URL=, PORT=3000, JWT_SECRET=, FCM_SERVER_KEY=
tsconfig.json                  в†ђ extends ../../tsconfig.base.json, adds decorators/metadata options
```

### `packages/types/`
